Nollywood actress, Tonto Dikeh, on Sunday lamented over the healthcare system in Nigeria. In her Instagram story, the actress lambasted an undisclosed hospital for refusing to treat an unnamed dying patient. According to her, the hospital demanded a sum of one million naira and she paid N500,000 cash and still gave them a cheque. The mother-of-one further stated that despite her payment, the hospital refused to attend to the patient. She then expressed her exasperation over the attitude of healthcare workers in hospitals. Dikeh wrote, “Our healthcare is ridiculously and painfully zero percent. How can a hospital refuse to treat a dying patient? “It’s not like you need to buy anything at the moment. I’m so sick and tired of dealing with these callous healthcare mishaps.” Sharing the screenshot of the story post on her feed, the actress wrote in the caption, “I don’t think I have been this pissed off in a while.” Nollywood actress, Tonto Dikeh says she is the most controversial person on earth. Dikeh spoke in a video at the TEDx Ikenegbu programme titled “Leveraging on Controversy’, which she posted on her official Instagram page @tontolet. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that the programme is an annual event… In "Entertainment" Nollywood actress, Tonto Dikeh, has revealed that she had, at a point in her life, ignored the ‘bad’ in someone because she loved them. The mother-of-one revealed this on her verified Instagram page on Monday, explaining that such a decision was the most toxic thing she had ever done. “One… In "Entertainment" The Nigerian Christian Pilgrim Commission (NCPC) has denied appointing Nollywood actress, Tonto Dikeh, as its peace ambassador. Recall that the movie star broke the news of her appointment in an Instagram post on Friday and shared a picture of herself alongside Yakubu Pam, the executive secretary of the NCPC, during… In "News"